#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:83
#: 42d77d5ce146424abe88acdac5b1db36
msgid "Getting to the boot screen"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:86
#: d7324c9042af413499750af48940e963
msgid ""
"“Booting” is the process of starting your computer. When a computer boots"
" up, it first runs low-level software before the main operating system. "
"Depending on the computer, this low-level software may be called the "
"`“BIOS” <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BIOS>`__ or `“UEFI” "
"<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unified_Extensible_Firmware_Interface>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:88
#: 25a513ce7b5b4acd899594815f8f0a80
msgid ""
"Since you’re installing Qubes OS, you’ll need to access your computer’s "
"BIOS or UEFI menu so that you can tell it to boot from the USB drive to "
"which you just copied the Qubes installer ISO."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:90
#: 1f01a18cde484d7797e2183e31208be7
msgid ""
"To begin, power off your computer and plug the USB drive into a USB port,"
" but don’t press the power button yet. Right after you press the power "
"button, you’ll have to immediately press a specific key to enter the BIOS"
" or UEFI menu. The key to press varies from brand to brand. ``Esc``, "
"``Del``, and ``F10`` are common ones. If you’re not sure, you can search "
"the web for ``<COMPUTER_MODEL> BIOS key`` or ``<COMPUTER_MODEL> UEFI "
"key`` (replacing ``<COMPUTER_MODEL>`` with your specific computer model) "
"or look it up in your computer’s manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:92
#: 6c4e6f3a4dd24388984657e704ec07bb
msgid ""
"Once you know the key to press, press your computer’s power button, then "
"repeatedly press that key until you’ve entered your computer’s BIOS or "
"UEFI menu. To give you an idea of what you should be looking for, we’ve "
"provided a couple of example photos below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:94
#: b8bc0e7157f545638ff53eb525603721
msgid "Here’s an example of what the BIOS menu looks like on a ThinkPad T430:"
msgstr ""

