#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:184
#: 211bdf5154f945c8afe8f55f6c31af2b
msgid ""
"Under the System section, you must choose the installation destination. "
"Select the storage device on which you would like to install Qubes OS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:188
#: d372d5d5dd68496b8238ae857938b751
msgid ""
"**Warning:** Be careful to choose the correct installation target, or you"
" may lose data. We strongly recommended making a full backup before "
"proceeding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:190
#: 704c87cacbb9493cb9ea30e6ef14906c
msgid ""
"Your installation destination can be an internal or external storage "
"drive, such as an SSD, HDD, or USB drive. The installation destination "
"must have a least 32 GiB of free space available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:194
#: d41deebd1e63488487a4e1644f88da0e
msgid ""
"**Note:** The installation destination cannot be the same as the "
"installation medium. For example, if you’re installing Qubes OS *from* a "
"USB drive *onto* a USB drive, they must be two distinct USB drives, and "
"they must both be plugged into your computer at the same time. (**Note:**"
" This may not apply to advanced users who partition their devices "
"appropriately.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:196
#: 47c2af4ec54d493789f39e350f4a6ebd
msgid ""
"Installing an operating system onto a USB drive can be a convenient way "
"to try Qubes. However, USB drives are typically much slower than internal"
" SSDs. We recommend a very fast USB 3.0 drive for decent performance. "
"Please note that a minimum storage of 32 GiB is required. If you want to "
"install Qubes OS onto a USB drive, just select the USB device as the "
"target installation device. Bear in mind that the installation process is"
" likely to take longer than it would on an internal storage device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:198
