#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:258
#: b9efa31154124757b3c5f6014d9be47f
msgid ""
"By default, the installer will create a number of qubes (depending on the"
" options you selected during the installation process). These are "
"designed to give you a more ready-to-use environment from the get-go."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:260
#: 53a6a9109fc54ebd8f62eb1d9445a070
msgid "Let’s briefly go over the options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:262
#: a5702c260ae048aba844f5b9b8a73bd9
msgid ""
"**Templates Configuration:** Here you can decide which :doc:`templates "
"</user/templates/templates>` you want to have installed, and which will "
"be the default template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:264
#: 2b47c14d63b04b758225d501eebb4e87
msgid ""
"**Create default system qubes:** These are the core components of the "
"system, required for things like internet access. You can opt to have "
"some created as :term:`disposables <disposable>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:266
#: 6150198733364a5bb69a436eff2fe63d
msgid ""
"**Create default application qubes:** These are how you compartmentalize "
"your digital life. There’s nothing special about the ones the installer "
"creates. They’re just suggestions that apply to most people. If you "
"decide you don’t want them, you can always delete them later, and you can"
" always create your own."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:268
#: e4e534eeecbf478d91bfd642aa2711ef
msgid ""
"**Use a qube to hold all USB controllers:** Just like the network qube "
"for the network stack, the USB qube isolates the USB controllers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:270
#: 6141ef5ecfa8486ebe6bb8a7e5c3a1f3
msgid ""
"**Use sys-net qube for both networking and USB devices:** You should "
"select this option if you rely on a USB device for network access, such "
"as a USB modem or a USB Wi-Fi adapter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:274
#: 7c503cda2bd3419bbf03b606e596037c
msgid ""
"**Create Whonix Gateway and Workstation qubes:** If you want to use "
"`Whonix <https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Qubes>`__, you should select this "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:276
#: d950560affe84e7087168f878a1cead5
msgid ""
"**Enabling system and template updates over the Tor anonymity network "
"using Whonix:** If you select this option, then whenever you install or "
"update software in dom0 or a template, the internet traffic will go "
"through Tor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:280
#: a79542bd656c409c9558a1cbd6625f0f
msgid ""
"**Do not configure anything:** This is for very advanced users only. If "
"you select this option, you will have to manually set up everything."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide.rst:284
#: 9abd6861bc2a421280de307cf1f8248a
msgid ""
"When you’re satisfied with your choices, press **Done**. This "
"configuration process may take a while, depending on the speed and "
"compatibility of your system."
msgstr ""

